         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="saint-1239" ana="#syriaca-saint">
               <persName xml:id="name1239-2" xml:lang="en">Ezechiel, monk</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1239-3" xml:lang="en">Ezechial</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1239-4" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1239-2">Ézéchiel, moine (de Daqoq ?)</persName>
               <persName xml:id="name1239-5" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib1239-1">ÉZÉCHIAL</persName>
               <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1239</idno>
               <idno type="FIEY">159</idno>
               <idno type="BHS">1210</idno>
               <sex value="M" source="#bib1239-1">male</sex>
               <floruit source="#bib1239-1" when="0363" syriaca-computed-start="0363">0363</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1239-1">Suhadii', II, 238-65, d'apres un manuscrit de Kerkouk du xne siecle. Pas dans
BHO.
Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, III, 64-67.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Ezekiel was a monk who was born on the same day as Constantine. He was a Jew from the tribe of Manasseh who went to Egypt and became a disciple of Mar Awgin. Awgin and his disciples left for the region of Adiabene and Beth Garmai. They went to Mahoze and baptized the entire city, after they healed the sick. Ezekiel went around the region converting the "Magians." He founded a monastery near Daduq. He ended his life near Kirkuk.</note>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1239-1">
                  <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Bibliotheca Hagiographica Syriaca</title>
                  <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/649"/>
                  <citedRange unit="entry">1210</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1239-2">
                  <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                  <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">ÉZÉCHIAL</title>
                  <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                  <citedRange unit="entry">159</citedRange>
               </bibl>
               <title>Shuhadā'</title>
               <citedRange> II, 238-65</citedRange>
               <note>From a manuscript from Kirkuk from the 12th century. It is not in the BHO.</note>
               <bibl xml:id="bib1239-4">
                  <author>Fiey</author>
                  <title>Assyrie chretienne</title>
                  <citedRange>III, 64-67.</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
